[[/HIGH_LEVEL_REQUIREMENT]]

[[HIGH_LEVEL_REQUIREMENT]]
UID: HLR-PIPE-010
TITLE: Relation Type Inference
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall infer relation types during the ANALYZE Phase phase using constraint-based matching with Specificity Scoring scoring.
<<<
DESCRIPTION: >>>
For each unresolved relation, the relation analyzer:

Filter: Identifies candidate relation types whose constraints are compatible with the relation’s TERM-SELECTOR, source attribute, source type, and target type
Resolve: Calls the resolver (determined by the type’s extends chain root) to find the target object
Score: Counts matching non-NULL constraints across all four dimensions; NULL constraints act as wildcards (match anything but do not increase specificity)
Pick: The highest specificity match wins; ties mark the relation as ambiguous

Same-specification targets are preferred over cross-specification targets. The relation’s target_ref and type_ref are updated in the database.
<<<
RATIONALE: >>>
Type inference from constraints eliminates explicit relation type annotation in source documents, reducing authoring burden. Specificity scoring ensures the most specific matching type is selected, enabling both generic and specialized relation types to coexist.
<<<
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: TERM-SELECTOR
  ROLE: Dictionary Reference
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: TERM-20
  ROLE: Dictionary Reference
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: TERM-SPECIFICITY
  ROLE: Dictionary Reference
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SF-001
  ROLE: Belongs To

[[/HIGH_LEVEL_REQUIREMENT]]

